subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalic veil oval, free from operculum, with 9–20 smooth cirri (
holotype
11) on anterior and lateral margins (
Figs 31F–G
; 
32A
; 
33C
). Pair of ear-shaped lobes adjacent to both sides of dorsal base of cephalic veil (
Fig. 33I
). Buccal tentacles broad and short, with long mid-groove, arising from posterior to cephalic veil, extending to margin of cephalic veil (
Figs 31F–G
; 
32A
; 
33C
).

